    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img 
      src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dphbnwjtx/image/upload/v1740598472/henrique-ferreira-6v-K4PpCHVw-unsplash_1_zkpj2a.webp"
      alt="Zurich cityscape with lake and mountains"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-black/60 to-black/40" />
    </div>
    
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-24 md:py-32">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold text-white mb-6">
          <span class="block">Expat Insurance & Living in</span>
          <span class="block mt-2">Zurich Guide <span class="text-primary-500">2025</span></span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-lg mx-auto text-xl text-gray-300">
          Your essential companion for navigating insurance, housing, and daily life in Switzerland's largest city.
        </p>
        
        <!-- Quick Stats -->
        <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
          {quickStats.map((stat) => (
          <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-lg p-4">
            <dt class="text-gray-300 text-sm">{stat.label}</dt>
            <dd class="text-white font-bold text-xl">{stat.value}</dd>
          </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <div class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Introduction: Living in Zurich as an Expat</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>
          Zurich, Switzerland's largest city and financial capital, consistently ranks among the world's most livable cities. With its stunning location on Lake Zurich, surrounded by the Alps, the city offers an exceptional quality of life, combining urban sophistication with natural beauty.
        </p>
        <p>
          Home to numerous multinational companies, leading universities, and a thriving startup scene, Zurich attracts professionals from around the globe. While the city's efficient public transport, excellent healthcare, and high standard of living are major draws, understanding the Swiss insurance system is crucial for a smooth transition and comfortable life in Zurich.
        </p>
        <p>
          This comprehensive guide will help you navigate both the essentials of living in Zurich and its specific insurance requirements. Whether you're planning your move or already settling in, we'll provide the information you need to make informed decisions about health insurance, housing, and other practical aspects of expat life in Zurich.
        </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Understanding Mandatory Insurance Section -->
  <div class="bg-gray-50 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Understanding Mandatory Insurance in Zurich for Expats</h2>
        
        <!-- Health Insurance Subsection -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">Swiss Health Insurance (KVG/LAMal) in Zurich: A Must-Have</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg mb-8">
          <p>
            Health insurance (Krankenversicherung/Assurance-maladie) is mandatory for all residents in Zurich. You must obtain coverage within three months of arrival, and it's retroactive to your arrival date.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Key Facts About Swiss Health Insurance in Zurich</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Registration Deadline:</strong> Within 3 months of arrival</li>
              <li><strong>Basic Coverage:</strong> Identical across all insurers (legally defined)</li>
              <li><strong>Average Monthly Premium:</strong> CHF 300-500 (among the highest in Switzerland)</li>
              <li><strong>Deductible Options:</strong> CHF 300-2,500 annually (higher deductible = lower premium)</li>
              <li><strong>Co-payment:</strong> 10% of costs above your deductible (up to CHF 700 annually)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Insurance Models Available in Zurich</h4>
          <p>Zurich offers several insurance models, each with different premium levels:</p>
          
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="min-w-full bg-white rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md">
              <thead class="bg-gray-100">
                <tr>
                  <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Model</th>
                  <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Description</th>
                  <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left">Cost Level</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4"><strong>Standard</strong></td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">Free choice of doctors throughout Switzerland</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">Highest premiums</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4"><strong>Family Doctor</strong></td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">First consult your chosen general practitioner</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">10-15% lower premiums</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4"><strong>HMO</strong></td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">Use specific health centers as first point of contact</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">15-20% lower premiums</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4"><strong>Telmed</strong></td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">Call medical hotline before seeing a doctor</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">15-20% lower premiums</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          
          <p class="mt-6">
            Zurich has excellent medical facilities, with many healthcare providers offering English-speaking services. While premiums are higher than in most Swiss cantons, the quality of care is exceptional.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary-500 mt-6">
            <p class="text-primary-800 font-medium">
              <strong>Expat Tip:</strong> Consider an HMO or Telmed model if you're comfortable with these restrictions. The savings can be substantial, and many HMO centers in Zurich offer services in English.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mb-12 text-center">
          <a href="/blog/health-insurance-models-switzerland" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-md text-white bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors">
            Learn More About Insurance Models
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Accident Insurance Subsection -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">Accident Insurance (UVG/LAA) in Zurich: Workplace & Leisure Coverage</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg mb-12">
          <p>
            Accident insurance in Switzerland is divided into two components:
          </p>
          
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Occupational Accident Insurance (BU):</strong> Covers accidents that occur during work hours</li>
            <li><strong>Non-occupational Accident Insurance (NBU):</strong> Covers accidents during leisure time</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>
            If you work at least 8 hours per week for the same employer in Zurich, your employer must provide both occupational and non-occupational accident insurance. If you work fewer hours or are self-employed, you need to ensure accident coverage through your health insurance.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mt-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Why Accident Insurance is Crucial in Zurich</h4>
            <p>
              Zurich offers numerous outdoor activities given its proximity to mountains and lakes. Whether you're skiing in the nearby Alps, hiking, or cycling around Lake Zurich, having proper accident coverage is essential for enjoying Zurich's active lifestyle safely.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mb-12 text-center">
          <a href="/blog/accident-insurance-switzerland-uvg-laa" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-md text-white bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors">
            Explore Accident Insurance Details
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Essential Voluntary Insurance Section -->
  <div class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Essential Voluntary Insurance for Comfortable Living in Zurich</h2>
        
        <!-- Personal Liability Subsection -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">Personal Liability Insurance: Protecting You in Zurich</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg mb-8">
          <p>
            While not legally mandatory, personal liability insurance (Privathaftpflichtversicherung) is highly recommended in Switzerland and often expected by landlords in Zurich.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">What Personal Liability Insurance Covers</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Damage to your rental property (e.g., broken fixtures, water damage)</li>
              <li>Accidental harm to other people</li>
              <li>Damage to others' property</li>
              <li>Legal defense costs if you're sued for damages</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              In Zurich's high-cost environment, liability claims can be substantial. Most policies provide coverage of at least CHF 3-5 million, with annual premiums typically ranging from CHF 100-200.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mb-12 text-center">
          <a href="/insurance/personal-liability-insurance" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-md text-white bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors">
            Learn More About Liability Insurance
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Household Contents Subsection -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">Household Contents Insurance: Securing Your Zurich Home</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg mb-8">
          <p>
            Household contents insurance (Hausratversicherung) protects your personal belongings against risks like theft, fire, and water damage. In Zurich's expensive housing market, furnishing a home represents a significant investment that deserves protection.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">What Household Contents Insurance Covers in Zurich</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Furniture and home furnishings</li>
              <li>Electronics and appliances</li>
              <li>Clothing and personal items</li>
              <li>Valuable items (with potential limits or special conditions)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              Premiums are based on the total value of your belongings and the size of your home. For a typical 2-bedroom apartment in Zurich with contents worth CHF 50,000, expect to pay around CHF 150-300 annually.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary-500 mt-6">
            <p class="text-primary-800 font-medium">
              <strong>Expat Tip:</strong> Many insurance companies offer combined packages for personal liability and household contents insurance at competitive rates. This is often the most cost-effective option for expats in Zurich.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mb-12 text-center">
          <a href="/insurance/household-insurance" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-md text-white bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors">
            Explore Household Insurance Options
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Supplementary Health Insurance -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">Supplementary Health Insurance Options for Expats in Zurich</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg mb-8">
          <p>
            While basic health insurance covers essential medical needs, many expats in Zurich opt for supplementary health insurance (Zusatzversicherung) to enhance their coverage and comfort.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Popular Supplementary Coverage in Zurich</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Hospital Insurance:</strong> Access to private or semi-private rooms in Zurich's top hospitals</li>
              <li><strong>Dental Care:</strong> Coverage for dental treatments not included in basic insurance</li>
              <li><strong>Alternative Therapies:</strong> Coverage for treatments like osteopathy, acupuncture, or homeopathy</li>
              <li><strong>Vision Care:</strong> Contributions to eyeglasses or contact lenses</li>
              <li><strong>International Coverage:</strong> Extended coverage when traveling outside Switzerland</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <p>
            Unlike basic insurance, supplementary coverage is not guaranteed. Insurers can reject applications based on medical history or impose waiting periods or exclusions for pre-existing conditions.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary-500 mt-6">
            <p class="text-primary-800 font-medium">
              <strong>Expat Tip:</strong> Apply for supplementary insurance when you're in good health, as the approval process involves medical underwriting. If you have pre-existing conditions, work with a broker who can help find the best options.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Legal Protection Insurance -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">Legal Protection Insurance in Zurich</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg mb-12">
          <p>
            Legal protection insurance (Rechtsschutzversicherung) covers legal costs for certain types of disputes. For expats navigating Zurich's complex legal and administrative landscape, this can provide valuable peace of mind.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Common Situations Where Legal Protection Helps</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Rental disputes with landlords (common in Zurich's competitive housing market)</li>
              <li>Employment conflicts</li>
              <li>Consumer protection issues</li>
              <li>Contract disagreements</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              Annual premiums typically range from CHF 200-400, depending on the scope of coverage. Given the high cost of legal services in Zurich, this insurance can be a worthwhile investment.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
